<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910508-0018</DOCNO><DOCID>910508-0018.</DOCID><HL>   Marketing Brief -- NHI Nelson Holdings International:   New Line Cinema to Get   Movie Distribution Rights</HL><DATE>05/08/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE B6</SO><CO>   NLN NNH T.NNH</CO><MS>CONSUMER CYCLICAL (CYC)</MS><IN>ENTERTAINMENT AND LEISURE (ENT)RECREATION, ENTERTAINMENT, TOYS, MOVIES, PHOTOGRAPHY, SPORTS (REC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>CANADA (CN)NEW YORK (NY)</RE><LP>   NHI Nelson Holdings International Ltd., Toronto, said itentered into an agreement with New Line Cinema Corp.,granting New Line exclusive rights to distribute and managecertain of its motion pictures and other related products.   The agreement paves the way for a sale of a controllinginterest in the company's troubled Nelson EntertainmentHoldings Inc. subsidiary to New Line. NHI Nelson, in turn,will receive a $12 million infusion of cash to help it paydown a $99 million debt to its primary banker, CreditLyonnais Bank Nederland N.V.</LP><TEXT>   The agreement with New Line requires that NHI Nelson'sdistribution proceeds, after deducting certain expenses andfees, first be applied toward repaying Credit Lyonnais.   Under the agreement, NHI Nelson must sell its entire stakeor a majority of Nelson Entertainment Holdings shares to athird party approved by Credit Lyonnais and New Line by theend of the year. New Line will receive a $100,000 call rightduring November for all of NHI Nelson's shares in the NelsonEntertainment Holdings subsidiary. Upon exercise of thatright, NHI Nelson would be released from liability under thecredit facility.</TEXT></DOC>